{"nodes": [{"id": "stock_market_trend_analysis_reports_milestones_m2_report", "label": "M2 Report \u2014 Exploratory Data Analysis", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "Stock-Market-Trend-Analysis/reports/milestones/M2.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "stock_market_trend_analysis_reports_milestones_m2_volatility_clustering", "label": "Volatility Clustering (Conditional Heteroskedasticity)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Stock-Market-Trend-Analysis/reports/milestones/M2.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "ARCH-LM p~0 and ACF(r^2) lag-1 up to 0.487 for every ticker: returns are stationary in mean but conditionally heteroskedastic. Next-day variance is strongly predictable \u2014 the single most important result for model selection, motivating a GARCH variance model."}, {"id": "stock_market_trend_analysis_reports_milestones_m2_leverage_effect", "label": "Leverage Effect (Asymmetric Volatility)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Stock-Market-Trend-Analysis/reports/milestones/M2.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Down days raise next-day volatility more than up days (significant all 4 tickers, p 7e-6..0.035), so a symmetric GARCH(1,1) would miss the asymmetry \u2014 recommend EGARCH/GJR-GARCH (o=1)."}, {"id": "stock_market_trend_analysis_reports_milestones_m2_mutual_information", "label": "Mutual-Information Feature Ranking", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Stock-Market-Trend-Analysis/reports/milestones/M2.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Pearson is ~0 for every feature and hid the signal; MI shows volatility features carry ~67x the shuffle noise floor (parkinson_vol_21 MI=0.16 vs Pearson ~0.01). This n